  "market_context": "Tuesday, 12 September 2023, during NY session. Price had formed equal highs as draw-on liquidity, then swept a lower low, followed by displacement up and formation of a bullish breaker block overlapping a fair value gap.",
  "key_observation": "Price formed a bullish breaker block (low-high-lower low-higher high) that overlapped with a fair value gap (Unicorn confluence), and price respected the mean threshold of the up-close candles on retest.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified equal highs as draw-on liquidity for the NASDAQ 1-minute chart.",
    "Step 2: Observed price forming a lower low, then displacing upward through an up-close candle series, confirming a change in state of delivery.",
    "Step 3: Marked a fair value gap created by the displacement move and identified a breaker block (low-high-lower low-higher high sequence) overlapping it — the 'Unicorn' confluence.",
    "Step 4: Noted that price retested the zone without closing below the mean threshold of the up-close candles, validating the setup.",
    "Step 5: Entered long with stop placed just below the breaker block low, targeting the equal highs (draw-on liquidity)."
  ],
  "outcome": "Hit target at 2.14R; trade was successful.",
  "lessons": "The Unicorn setup—confluence of breaker block and FVG—provides high-probability entries when price respects the mean threshold on retest. Tight stops below the breaker low and targeting prior equal highs yield strong risk-reward.",
